{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 12 demonstrates the effect of different macro-parameters on the magnification maps in the case where the whole mass is in the form of microlenses, i.e.",
    "κ c = 0 in Eq.",
    "The density of the caustics is proportional to the total magnification (and consequently the number of microlenses from Eq.",
    "(13)), whose contours are shown in the top panel of Fig. 13.",
    "The effect of the shear is also striking, stretching the caustics and producing stratified maps with elongated \"filaments\" of caustics interspaced with demagnification troughs."
  ]
}